Package application

Class ReviewerWeight

java.lang.Object
application.ReviewerWeight
public class ReviewerWeight extends Object
ReviewerWeight represents the weight/trust level a student assigns to a specific reviewer. This allows students to prioritize reviews from reviewers they trust more.

  • Constructor Details

    • ReviewerWeight

      public ReviewerWeight(String studentUserName, String reviewerUserName, double weight)
      Creates a new ReviewerWeight for assigning a trust level to a reviewer. Timestamps are automatically set to the current time.
      Parameters:
      studentUserName - the username of the student assigning the weight
      reviewerUserName - the username of the reviewer being weighted
      weight - the trust level value (typically between 0.1 and 5.0)

    • ReviewerWeight

      public ReviewerWeight(int reviewerWeightId, String studentUserName, String reviewerUserName, double weight, LocalDateTime createdAt, LocalDateTime updatedAt)
      Creates a ReviewerWeight from existing database data. Used when loading weights from the database.
      Parameters:
      reviewerWeightId - the unique identifier from the database
      studentUserName - the username of the student who assigned the weight
      reviewerUserName - the username of the reviewer
      weight - the trust level value
      createdAt - the timestamp when this weight was first created
      updatedAt - the timestamp when this weight was last modified
